net.gini.android.capture.accounting.network

Class GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.gini.android.capture.accounting.network.GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GiniCaptureNetworkService

    public class GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService
extends java.lang.Object
implements GiniCaptureNetworkService
    Implementation using the Gini Accounting API of the network related tasks required by the Gini Capture SDK.

    Relies on the Gini Pay API lib for executing the requests, which implements communication with the Gini Accounting API using generated anonymous Gini users.

    Important: Access to the Gini User Center API is required which is restricted to selected clients only. Contact Gini if you require access.

    To create an instance use the GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService.Builder returned by the GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService.builder(Context) method.

    In order for the Gini Capture SDK to use this implementation pass an instance of it to GiniCapture.Builder#setGiniCaptureNetworkService(GiniCaptureNetworkService) when creating a GiniCapture instance.

      • getAnalyzedCameraPictureAsJpeg

        public byte[] getAnalyzedCameraPictureAsJpeg()
        Get the last successfully analyzed picture taken by the camera.

        Important: Call this method before calling GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService.cleanup() (or GiniCapture#cleanup(Context)), otherwise it will return null.

        Returns:
        a byte array containing the picture in jpeg format. Returns null, if GiniCaptureAccountingNetworkService.cleanup() (or GiniCapture#cleanup(Context)) was called before or the analyzed document was not an image taken by the camera with the Gini Capture SDK.
